‘I’ve tried to take some of that experience into it.

‘I was lucky to have so many great coaches, great managers that I worked under and at the right stage of my career as well.

‘You try and think about what would they have said to me at that particular time - what would he have done. But I’ve had a few bad ones along the way too. I’ve seen first-hand the wrong way to do things. You can’t have it all good.

Despite fans calling for him to be sacked, Pardew's side are now on a run of six successive victories

